  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Manager",
  "description": "<ul><li><p>Prepare and manage the overall project control plan, construction programme, and quality and safety plans.</p></li><li><p>Monitor progress and ensure works are carried out according to approved schedules and standards.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Organise and manage project production activities, including material approvals, sample submissions, and site implementation.</p></li><li><p>Oversee on-site construction activities from commencement to completion.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Coordinate and support the implementation of project design schemes.</p></li><li><p>Provide practical input and recommendations on drawings and construction details.</p></li><li><p>Participate in coordination with consultants and external parties on key milestones and technical matters.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Coordinate and manage on-site work with the main contractor, sub-contractors, consultants, and other stakeholders.</p></li><li><p>Resolve site and coordination issues to ensure smooth project execution.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Control and manage project cost budgets in accordance with company requirements.</p></li><li><p>Monitor variations, claims, and contract compliance to ensure commercial objectives are met.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Organise and allocate responsibilities among project team members.</p></li><li><p>Ensure manpower and resources are efficiently deployed to meet project needs.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Provide recommendations on project sub-contracting.</p></li><li><p>Oversee and manage sub-contractors to ensure performance, quality, safety, and cost control.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Carry out other duties assigned by management.</p></li><li><p>Participate in the development and improvement of the company’s project management systems and processes.</p></li></ul>",
